# Quality Assurance Checklist

**Purpose:** Universal QA checks for all task completions.

---

## Task Completion

- [ ] All requested tasks completed
- [ ] No tasks skipped or partially executed

---

## File Organization

- [ ] All output files in `notes/` folder (or same directory as input PDF for referee reports)
- [ ] Files organized appropriately (reading order where applicable)
- [ ] No orphan files created outside expected locations

### Referee Report Files (when applicable)
- [ ] Senior report: `{short_title}_claude_senior_report.tex` with Deal Breakers section
- [ ] Junior report: `{short_title}_claude_junior_report.tex` with Deal Breakers section
- [ ] Editor letter: `{short_title}_claude_editor_letter.tex` with synthesized recommendation
- [ ] All three files use same short_title prefix
- [ ] Each Deal Breaker includes "Why this affects publishability" explanation
- [ ] Signature image copied to output directory for editor letter compilation

---

## Content Quality

- [ ] Paper type context applied correctly throughout analysis
- [ ] Analysis depth meets quality standards
- [ ] LaTeX conventions followed (if applicable)
- [ ] Economics field conventions applied

---

## User Communication

- [ ] User informed of key findings
- [ ] Priority recommendations provided
- [ ] Next steps suggested
- [ ] Clear summary of what was done

---

## Validation Protocol

**IF ANY CHECKLIST ITEM FAILS:**
1. Stop immediately
2. Fix the issue
3. Re-run validation
4. Do NOT proceed to delivery until ALL checks pass
